${h2('Pathogens, Toxins and Drugs')}
    
    
    ${h3('Pathogens')}
    
    <p>Pathogens are infectious agents, or germs.  Viruses, bacteria and fungi are all examples
    of pathogens and are covered by these rules.</p>
    
    <p>Pathogens have a power based around the particular agents properties.  The power determines
    the TGN to resist the disease infecting the character which is a CONS roll.  If the the character
    fails then they have contracted the disease and suffers the effects in the pathogens description.
    CONS booster allows a character to completely resist infection by pathogens with a power up to
    the same level as the CONS booster.</p>
    
    <p>The character can be treated if infected.  First of all the medical practitioner needs to
    make a JUDG task roll to identify the agent, so it can be appropriately treated.  If they pass
    then the character makes a CONS test against a new TGN dependent upon the facilities available.
    The better the facilities the lower the TGN.</p>

