    ${h3('Toxins')}
    
    <p>Toxins are substances which have a negative effect on body chemistry and use exactly the
    same mechanics as Pathogens. The only difference is that their power is determined by different
    properties.</p>

    ${h3('Drugs')}
    
    <p>Whereas toxins have a completely negative effect on the human body, drugs usually produce
    a desirable change. In roleplaying games characters usually take drugs for reasons other
    than recreation.  So we have focused on drugs that produce desirable effects, such as painkillers
    and enhancers, but have included some recreational drugs for roleplaying purposes.</p>
    
    <p>When a character takes a drug they must first make a CONS roll against the addiction rating of
    the drug.  If they fail, and become addicted to the drug, then they need to take note of the withdrawal
    times of the drug.  If the character does not recieve another dose before the end of the withdrawal
    time then they suffer the withdrawal effects.  If they still fail to recive a dose before the long
    term withdrawal time then they suffer the long term withdrawal effects.  Regardless the effect of
    the drug is noted in it's description and the length of time this lasts for is given in the effect
    duration.</p>
    
